<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1435,1837,2005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">
Published records: “Kirjat Anawim” [Qiryat Anavim] (Verhoeff 
<number box="[874,932,1837,1861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" value="1934.0">1934</number>
, sub 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1296,1837,1861]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="flavidus" subSpecies="porosus">
<emphasis box="[990,1296,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Geophilus flavidus porosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). New records: none.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1435,1837,2005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[372,439,1909,1933]" name="Israel" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Israel</collectingCountry>
: known only from a single locality in the Jerusalem mountains (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1251,1909,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1132,1155]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,197,1108]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1111]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Collection maps for rarely collected species (one or two localities). A) Mediterranean and montane species. B) Desert species." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219931/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">
Figure 
<number box="[1236,1251,1909,1933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="236" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Global distribution: outside 
<collectingCountry box="[534,599,1945,1969]" name="Israel" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Israel</collectingCountry>
, published records are from the Carpathians and 
<collectingCountry box="[1198,1295,1945,1969]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="236">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
but require confirmation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="5" pageNumber="237">
Taxonomic and nomenclatural notes. Originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[1086,1298,152,176]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Geophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavidus">
<emphasis box="[1086,1298,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="237">Geophilus flavidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has long been a taxon of uncertain status and identity. After a comparative reassessment of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1176,1303,188,212]" class="Chilopoda" family="Geophilidae" genus="Clinopodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="5" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1303,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="237">Clinopodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it has been recognized as a distinct species, while rejecting the name 
<emphasis box="[798,885,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="237">porosus</emphasis>
because of homonymy (Bonato 
<emphasis box="[1250,1299,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="237">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1313,1373,223,247]" pageId="5" pageNumber="237" value="2011.0">2011</number>
).
</paragraph>
